---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have
2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4). Dice @Roma tomato{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.
Quarter @lemon{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1} into strips.

In a #small bowl{}, combine minced onion, tomato, half the cilantro, and a
squeeze of lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} with a squeeze of
lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until
mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with @olive oil{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings);
brush or rub to coat all over. Arrange on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer
(divide between 2 sheets for 4). Gently prick each tortilla in a few places with
a #fork{}.

Bake on top rack, flipping halfway through, until toasted and lightly golden,
~{4-5%minutes} per side. (For 4, bake on top and middle racks; flipping tortillas
and swapping rack positions halfway through.)

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

While tortillas bake, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a
#large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano, sliced onion, and half the
@Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step).
Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.
Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse @black beans{13.4%ounce}.

Heat pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add beans, @Tex-Mex paste{1},
remaining Southwest spice, and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Bring
to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has mostly evaporated,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat; gently mash beans with a #potato masher{} or back of a spoon.
Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}(until melted) (2 TBSP for 4). (TIP: If mixture is
too thick, stir in a splash of water.) Season with salt and pepper.

Once tortillas are toasted, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully spread each
tortilla with smashed beans, then top with veggies and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Return to top rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide tostadas between plates. Top with pico de gallo, lemon crema, and
remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.